# Contributing to JavaKids Lite

Thank you for your interest in contributing to JavaKids Lite.

This project is in the early prototype phase and contributions are limited until the core structure is fully defined.  
However, feedback and small improvements are welcome.

## How to Contribute

### 1. Open an Issue
If you want to suggest a feature or report a bug, please create a GitHub Issue with:
- a clear title  
- a short description  
- steps to reproduce the issue if relevant  

### 2. Pull Requests
Pull requests may be accepted for:
- small code improvements  
- UI enhancements  
- documentation fixes  

Please keep pull requests small and focused so they can be reviewed easily.

### 3. Style
There is no strict coding style yet, but please:
- keep code readable  
- use clear names  
- avoid unnecessary complexity  

### 4. Communication
This project is developed by a single founder so response times may vary.  
All valid contributions will be reviewed.

Thank you for helping improve JavaKids Lite.
